350 g Cheese Tortellini
237 mL Cream
113 g Baby Tomatoes
56 g Green Peas
1 tbsp Italian Seasoning
7 g Parsley
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add tortellini to the boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 2-3 min.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain.
Return tortellini to the same pot, off heat.
Add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter. Stir to coat.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add sausage and tomatoes to the pan. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until tomatoes have softened, and sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min.**

Add cream, garlic puree and Italian Seasoning.
Cook stirring often until sauce thickens slightly, 2-3 min.
Meanwhile, roughly chop parsley.

Add sauce, parsley and reserved pasta water to the large pot with the tortellini.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Divide tortellini between bowls. Sprinkle Parmesan over top.

If you've opted to add sausage, when the pan is hot, add sausage along with tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until tomatoes have softened and sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min**. Follow the rest of the recipe as written.